        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 3 at 2:54PM PDT by NWS Los Angeles/Oxnard CA</headline>
        <description>At 252 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Mount Baldy to 9 miles southeast of Acton.
These storms were slowly moving southward and westward.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail. Minor flooding.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
San Dimas...
Glendora...
Pomona...
Mount Wilson...
La Verne...
Azusa...
Falling Springs...
Angeles Crest Highway between Mount Wilson and Mount Waterman...
Monrovia...
Covina...
Claremont...
Diamond Bar...
Angeles Crest Highway between Mount Waterman and Wrightwood...
Duarte...
Irwindale...
and Walnut.

This also includes the south side of the Bridge Burn Scar.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
